The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Cipla offers 3:2 bonus 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Feb. 11: Cipla Ltd, the countrys fourth largest pharmaceutical company, today declared bonus shares in the ratio of three shares for every two shares held. 

 The company is also planning to raise funds from overseas markets by issuing either Global Depository Receipts (GDR) or American Depository Receipts (ADR). However, the company didnt disclose the size of the proposed ADR/GDR flotation. 

 The Cipla board today also approved a proposal to raise the foreign institutional investor (FII) limit to 40 per cent from the existing 24 per cent. At present, the promoters hold a 40.94 per cent stake in the company. The institutional investors own 29.37 per cent. 




